We’re looking back today at @amythystkiah’s powerful field recording of “Wild Turkey”, recorded in Johnson City, TN.

The subject matter of this tune is as heavy as it gets - the unimaginable anguish of losing a mother, and the years it takes to come to terms with it.

“Processing grief is one of the more difficult challenges in life.” Amythyst says, “Many of us get stuck in one stage and ultimately the pain ends up defining who we are. The sooner we can learn to process and find meaning in our lives again, the better we can be to ourselves and each other. This song was one of many processes, as there is never just one process. Here’s to hoping you find yours, whatever that may be.”

We’re certainly grateful to Amythyst for writing this moving song, and reminding us of the solace that music can bring during the tough times. Revisit this one in our bio link, and check out all of Amythyst’s tunes whenever you listen to things. She’s also heading out to the UK soon for a series of epic shows, go check those tickets out.

I hope you take the time to call somebody you love today and catch up. They might not be around as long as you hope - make the most of it.

cheers,
@matthewkfowler

Holler Live Sessions: Presenting @amythystkiah ❤️‍🔥

Playing Firewater, Hangover Blues and Wild Turkey, Amythyst proves just why she is one of the most celebrated singers and guitarists around right now. 🔥

From embracing Black identity as an artist to overcoming the social anxiety, grief and alienation that defined her formative years, Amythyst’s music masterfully recounts the pivotal moments in a life ultimately defined by reclamation and self acceptance.

Hit the 🔗 in our bio to tune in now.

I had an amazing time celebrating Sister Rosetta Tharpe’s legacy this past Sunday. As I worked up arrangements for my versions of the songs she sang (alongside reading her biography, Shout, Sister, Shout! By Gayle F. Wald, if you’re curious), I wanted to capture the spirit of rock and roll that she inspired so many of us to pursue. Knowing who you are and following your gift is my main takeaway from learning about her life and music, and how difficult it is but worth it to maintain that goal. Thanks to all that took part in this special event!

#gibson #sisterrosettatharpe #gibsongives

New shirt designs by @flomihr are hot off the press and available at shows and online (link in bio)! I’m a big believer in Memento Mori and self-mastery of the things we can control in life, as existence is in constant flux. Despite falling short many times, in keeping this in mind, getting back up and trying again is all we can do, because we’ve got at least one mortal life that we know we have. Let’s try to make the best of it. 🙂

Thanks again to Flo for matching my wavelength and creating designs that matches my galaxy brain ideas 🤓. Cheers!

P.S. I sized up and cropped the black T-shirt. I highly encourage modification to make the shirt fit your style! ✂️
